  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Directly learning the values in matrix p ∈ [0, 1] M×K is challenging due to the constraint that each column of p should be a valid probability distribution.",
    "We thus reparameterize matrix p ∈ [0, 1] M×K using another matrix ϕ 2 R M × K following Zhu et al.",
    "In this way, we turned the constrained optimization with respect to p into an unconstrained optimization with respect to ϕ:",
    "where α i is the parameter used for strengthening or reducing the diversity at residue i.",
    "By default, we set α i = 1/M, ∀ i, while in the 'informed setting' (Fig. 1b), researchers can vary α i to control residuelevel diversity, which cannot be achieved by many existing library design algorithms 34, 35, 55."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
